Lagerstroemia flos-reginae

    Authority
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Myrtales:Lythraceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 1317

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A tall deciduous tree with a rounded crown.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial.
   COMMON NAMES
   Jarul, Ajhar, Taman, Bondara, Hole-dasal, Challa, Pumarathu,
   Manimarthu, Pyinma, Eikmwe.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: L. speciosa. Jalur is best adapted to lowland
   conditions. Its natural range includes India, Sri Lanka, Bangladesh and
   Myanmar. It occur along river banks, streams and the edges of swampy
   ground, but thrives best on well drained soils. Yearly volume
   production may be 3-5 m3/ha.

   Sources
   SOURCES (L. flos-reginare Retz.)
   Troup R 1921 pp 598-601 [USE, DRA, FER, DEP, TEXT, TEMP, RAIN, LIG, PH]
   Zabala N 1990 pp 60-62 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, DEP, FER, LIG, KTMP,
   USE]

